Package org.flowable.dmn.api

Interface DmnDeployment

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.flowable.common.engine.api.repository.EngineDeployment
    public interface DmnDeployment
extends org.flowable.common.engine.api.repository.EngineDeployment
    Represents a deployment that is already present in the dmn repository. A deployment is a container for resources such as dmn definitions, images, forms, etc. When a deployment is 'deployed', the Flowable engine will recognize certain of such resource types and act upon them (eg decision tables will be parsed to an executable Java artifact). To create a Deployment, use the DmnDeploymentBuilder. A Deployment on itself is a read-only object and its content cannot be changed after deployment (hence the builder that needs to be used).
    Author:
    Tijs Rademakers, Joram Barrez
